anne Theatre]], New York City, New York, U.S. \n|Closed until 7 June 2020.\n|<ref name=\"cnn\" />\n|-\n|{{flagicon|United Kingdom}} [[Aldwych Theatre]], London, England\n|Closed until 31 May 2020.\n|<ref name=\"west end\" />\n|-\n|''[[To Kill a Mockingbird (2018 play)|To Kill a Mockingbird]]''\n|{{flagicon|United States}} [[Shubert Theatre (New York City)|Shubert Theatre]], New York City, New York, U.S. \n|Closed until 7 June 2020.\n|<ref name=\"cnn\" />\n|-\n|''[[Uncle Vanya]]'' (revival)\n|{{flagicon|United Kingdom}} [[Harold Pinter Theatre]], London, England\n|Closed until 31 May 2020.\n|<ref name=\"west end\" />\n|-\n|''The Upstart Crow''\n|{{flagicon|United Kingdom}} [[Gielgud Theatre]], London, England\n|Closed until 31 May 2020.\n|<ref name=\"west end\" />\n|-\n|''[[Waitress (musical)|Waitress]]''\n|{{flagicon|United Kingdom}} [[Adelphi Theatre]], London, England\n|Closed permanently after final performance on 16 March 2020<br/>[[Sara Bareilles]] and [[Gavin Creel]]'s limited run ended on 14 March 2020.\n|<ref>{{cite news|url= https://www.thestage.co.uk/news/2020/coronavirus-waitress-confirms-it-will-not-reopen-after-theatre-closures |title= Coronavirus: Waitress confirms it will not reopen after theatre closures|publisher=The Stage|last=Snow|first=Georgia|date=27 March 2020|accessdate=28 March 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n|''[[West Side Story]]'' (revival)\n|{{flagicon|United States}} [[Broadway Theatre (53rd Street)|Broadway Theatre]], New York City, New York, U.S. \n|Closed until 7 June 2020.\n|<ref name=\"cnn\" />\n|-\n|''[[Who's Afraid of Virginia Woolf?]]'' (revival)\n|{{flagicon|United States}} [[Booth Theatre]], New York City, New York, U.S. \n|Cancelled after 9 previews\n|<ref>[https://www.broadwayworld.com/article/WHOS-AFRAID-OF-VIRGINIA-WOOLF-Announces-Broadway-Closing-20200321 \" 'Who's Afraid of Virginia Woolf' Announces Broadway Closing\"] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200321125721/https://www.broadwayworld.com/article/WHOS-AFRAID-OF-VIRGI